                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On February 18, the Secretary of State announced the resignation of <persName
                        corresp="#p_COMPTONWS1">Wilson Compton</persName> as head of the
                    International Information Agency. Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName> stated that <persName corresp="#p_COMPTONWS1"
                        >Compton</persName>’s resignation had been submitted the previous month and
                    was being accepted in line with the new administration’s policy of bringing in
                    new people where major policy changes or views were involved. (<hi rend="italic"
                        >New York Times</hi>, February 19, 1953, page 1)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
